node.text:
Hummus dreams come true! Who else wants to dive into this homemade hummus by @naturallyzuzu? 😍🙋‍♀️. ・・・
Ingredients:
- 2 cans of chickpeas (drain one can and reserve water from the second can).
- 1 cup good quality tahini.
- Juice from one large lemon.
- Chickpea juice from the can.
- 3-4 cloves of garlic.
- 1-2 tsp salt.
- 1 tsp pepper.
.
Blend everything in a food processor until smooth and creamy. Plate the hummus in a shallow bowl, decorate with chopped purple onions, roasted chickpeas, cherry tomatoes, parsley, lemon wedges, and crushed red pepper. Enjoy with warm pita bread.
.
Recipe and photo by the amazing  @naturallyzuzu 🙌💞

node.text:
Did someone say Sushi Sandwiches?! 😳🤯😍 Pure genius from @foodie.yuki. 🍙🙌 Recipe below 👇.
.
Summer Teriyaki Onigirazu (sushi sandwiches) filled with mango + teriyaki tofu.
.
Here's👇🏻 the recipe for the teriyaki tofu
(Makes 4)
2 x 250g firm tofu
2 Tbsp mirin
2 Tbsp soy sauce 
2 Tbsp sake
4 Tbsp potato starch 
2 Tbsp coconut oil
.
Wrap the tofu with paper towels and place it on a plate. Weight it down with a heavy object for 30 min to drain the water. 
To make teriyaki sauce, combine sake, mirin and soy sauce.
Cut tofu horizontally (about 1 cm thick) then  into 10x10 cm square. 
Coat the tofu with the potato starch, shake off the excess. 
In a non-stick frying pan, heat 2 Tbsp oil on medium high heat.
Cook the tofu squares until the bottom side is golden brown. (About 3-4 min)
Flip and cook the other side. 
When both sides are golden brown, pour in the teriyaki sauce and coat evenly. 
Sprinkle with sesame seeds.”
.
Recipe and photo by the awe-inspiring Yuki ♡ @foodie.yuki. 💞

node.text:
Holy MOLY do these look 👀 Magnum-ificent. 😍🙌🍓🥥🍨 Recipe by @joyfulhomecooking below 👇.
.
Ingredients:
•1 cup raw cashews (soaked overnight)
•½ cup coconut cream
•600 g strawberries
•5-6 tbsp maple syrup
•2½ tsp agar agar powder
•½ pink pitaya powder for the color 
Choco Dip:
•200 g dairy-free dark chocolate
•2 tsp coconut oil
.
Method:
1. Refrigerate ice cream molds for at least an hour before you begin.
2. Take a small pot to mix agar powder and coconut cream. Place the pot on low-medium heat and allow the mixture to simmer. Stir frequently until the powder dissolves and the mixture thickens (10 mins).
⚠️Tip: Work fast since the agar sets quickly.
3. Chuck the remaining ingredients into a blender. Blend until they combine, then add the creamy mixture. Scrape the blender to prevent the ingredients from sticking.
4. Blend till you get a smooth creamy texture. Adjust sweetness by adding more maple syrup if required.
5. Pour the mixture into the chilled ice cream molds. Pop them into the freezer to set. (3-4 hours).
6. Melt your dark chocolate with coconut oil on top of a warm water bath.
7. Once the ice cream is set, dip it into the melted chocolate.
8. Pop it back into the freezer. (30 mins)
9. Defrost the bars at room temp before serving (min 1 hr).
.
Ta-da💁🏻‍♀️! The best part about this recipe is that it doesn’t need an ice cream maker.
.
Recipe and photo by @joyfulhomecooking 💞

node.text:
Brilliant “banana 🍌 boats” snack idea! 💡 This one comes from @earthofmariaa! 💞Forget toilet paper 🧻 , BANANAS have been the one item that make me and my hubby look like crazy hoarders at the grocery store. Little tip: get both ripe bananas AND green bananas that will ripen later and keep you home longer. 🏡 And of course freeze them when they get spotty, or if they get so ripe they’re black, use them for banana bread! There’s no reason to waste bananas, ever. - @MichelleCehn 👩🏼‍🌾 #zerowaste #stayhome #bananaboats #vegansnack #veganfood #whatveganseat #worldofvegan.
・・・
“From top to bottom there is peanut butter with strawberries, soy yogurt with blueberries and granola, peanut butter with raspberries, and soy yogurt with blueberries and pomegranate.“ - @earthofmariaa
